tive on political temporality allows us to better understand the formation of these biopolitical human rights violations and their exclusion from memory and historic justice.  afunded by transcript: Open Library 2021 (Politik)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aBiopolitics. 4aContemporary History. 4aHuman Rights Violations. 4aHuman Rights. 4aLaw. 4aMemory Culture. 4aNazi Crimes. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPolitical Temporality. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aBiopolitics.  aContemporary History.  aHuman Rights Violations.  aHuman Rights.  aLaw.  aMemory Culture.  aNazi Crimes.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Temporality.2 atranscript: Open Library 2021 (Politik)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839445501zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839445501zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839445501/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Par